<title type="html"><![CDATA[When Is A Deed An Act Of Worship? - al-Haafidh al-Hakamee [1377H] -Rahimullaah-]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1263&amp;p=1335#p1335"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">When is a deed an act of worship?</span></strong><br /><em>al-Haafidh al-Hakamee [1377H] -Rahimullaah-</em><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Question:</span></strong><br /><br />When is a deed an act of worship?<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Answer:</span></strong><br /><br />If two aspects are present: perfect love (for Allaah) combined with perfect humility (to Him). Allaah, the Most High, says:<br /><br /><ul><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">“But those who believe, love Allaah more (than anything else)”</span></strong> (al-Baqarah: 165)</ul><br />And He, the Most High, said:<br /><br /><ul><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">“Verily those who live in awe for fear of their Lord”</span></strong> (al-Mu'minun: 57)</ul><br />Allaah, the Most High, gathered these two aspects in His saying:<br /><br /><ul><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">“Verily, they used to hasten to good deeds, and they used to call upon Us with hope and fear, and used to humble themselves before Us”</span></strong> (al-Anbiyaa: 90)</ul><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">al-Haafidh al-Hakamee</span></strong><br /><em>A‘laam As-Sunnah Al-Manshoorah li I’tiqaad At-Taaifah An-Naajiyah Al-Mansoorah</em><br /><br />Translated by Abul-Irbaad Abid Zargar<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.fatwaislam.com/fis/index.cfm?scn=fd&amp;ID=156">http://www.fatwaislam.com/fis/index.cfm?scn=fd&amp;ID=156</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Thu Mar 09, 2017 2:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
